title: Suspected burglar found passed out in car in Seattle
text:
A 25-year-old man—suspected of committing three burglaries, a car prowl and an assault in the same night—was arrested after he was found ‘passed out in a car.’
Early Friday morning, a resident was awoken by a noise within her house.
She investigated and found dirty footprints on her carpet that led from an open window in the home to her front door.
#Seattle police arrest 25-year-old man passed out in car this morning -- suspected of 3 burglaries, car prowl, and assault, per @SeattlePD
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 9, 2015 Later on, after police responded to the woman’s report but were unable to locate a suspect, officers responded once again to the same building.
A man called saying he found a person asleep in a car inside the apartment’s secure parking garage.
When he confronted the sleeping person, he was attacked with a box cutter, an errant punch, and then a rock.
Police say he was not seriously injured in the attack—and chased after the suspect, who shouted death threats at him.
The suspect was caught and arrested.
On his person, police found a school ID and debit card belonging to a woman, and a lanyard from a University District church.
A woman confirmed her keys and bank card had been stolen from her apartment in the University District.
